sql:
SELECT name, total_personnel
FROM fire_departments
ORDER BY total_personnel DESC;

external_knowledge:
; Each fire department has a unique identifier (department_id); 
; Incident types are categorized and described in the incident_types table; 
; The reporting_year signifies the year an incident was reported, not necessarily when it occurred; 
; Incident types with only one incident are excluded to focus on recurring incident types.

- A fire department is a public or private organization that provides firefighting services to a specific geographic area; 
- An incident in this context refers to a specific event that prompts a firefighting response, which could range from actual fires to emergency medical responses;
- Property loss refers to damage to real estate or buildings, while contents loss refers to damage to items within those properties.
